OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be a dry day with some
OL,6,Fpatchy cloud allowing plenty of sunny
OL,7,Fspells to break through. Feeling warm,
OL,8,Fespecially in the sunshine. Light
OL,9,Fwinds.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA dry evening with late
OL,12,Fsunshine, then long clear spells after
OL,13,Fsunset. Overnight dry with long clear
OL,14,Fspells and a few mist and fog patches,
OL,15,Fthese mainly in the east.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FAny isolated mist and fog
OL,18,Fpatches will be quick clear leaving a
OL,19,Fdry day with light winds and
OL,20,Fpredominantly clear skies giving
OL,21,Fplenty of sunshine. Feeling warm.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
